.TH SCRIBE 1 "December 2025" "Scribe CLI 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
scribe \- terminal-based note access for Scribe app
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B scribe
.I command
[
.I arguments
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B scribe
provides a command-line interface to interact with your Scribe application notes database. It allows you to create, search, edit, and manage notes directly from your terminal.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B new "Title"
Create a new note in the inbox.
.TP
.B daily, d
Open or create today's daily note.
.TP
.B capture, c "Text"
Quickly capture a thought to the inbox. If no text is provided, reads from standard input.
.TP
.B search, s "Query"
Search notes using full-text search.
.TP
.B list, ls [folder]
List recent notes. Optionally filter by folder.
.TP
.B open, o "Title"
Open a note in the Scribe application.
.TP
.B edit, e "Title"
Edit a note using your default $EDITOR.
.TP
.B delete, del "Title"
Delete a note (move to trash).
.TP
.B export "Title"
Export a note's content to standard output.
.TP
.B browser
Run Scribe in a browser (Chrome or Brave).
.TP
.B backup [file]
Backup the database to a file.
.TP
.B restore <file>
Restore the database from a backup file.
.TP
.B tags, t
List all tags with note counts.
.TP
.B folders, f
List all folders with note counts.
.TP
.B stats
Show database statistics.
.TP
.B help
Show help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B scribe daily
.br
Open today's daily note.

.B scribe capture "Buy milk"
.br
Capture a task to the inbox.

.B scribe search "project"
.br
Search for notes containing "project".
.SH FILES
.I ~/Library/Application Support/com.scribe.app/scribe.db
.br
The SQLite database used by Scribe.
.SH AUTHOR
Stat-Wise
